    "id": "network-infiltration",
    "pack_id": "network-infiltration",
    "name": "Network Infiltration",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "In this challenge, you'll learn how to use Metasploit to perform a password brute force attack against an SSH server. You'll need to use the SSH login scanner module (auxiliary/scanner/ssh/ssh_login) with the username 'target' and the password list located at /home/kali/challenge/passwords.txt. Once you discover valid credentials, connect to the system using SSH and find the hidden flag file. This hands-on exercise demonstrates penetration testing techniques for identifying weak authentication implementations and highlights the importance of strong password policies.",
    "challenge_type": "metasploit",
    "difficulty": "beginner",
    "author": "EDURange Team",
    "estimated_time": 45
  },
